{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a Layer 3 VPN for customer 8803. Name it 'VPRN-8526-DataHub'. There's one site on device 192.168.130.48 with service ID 8526. Use RD 65108:8526, import policy DataHub-VRF-Import and export policy DataHub-VRF-Export. The interfaces are: Delta-Cluster-Master on port lag-Juniper6-4x10GE with IP 172.21.76.57/24; Delta-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-Arista11-4x10GE with IP 10.16.20.165/30."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-8526-DataHub\",\n    \"customer-id\": 8803,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-8526-DataHub\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.130.48\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 8526,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65108:8526\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"DataHub-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"DataHub-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Delta-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Juniper6-4x10GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"172.21.76.57\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 24,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Delta-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"lag-Arista11-4x10GE\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.prim