{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Create a VPRN L3 VPN service named 'VPRN-3188-QuantumNet' for customer 9085 with two sites. Site 1 on device 192.168.168.88 (service ID 3188, RD 64533:3188, VRF QuantumNet-VRF-Import/QuantumNet-VRF-Export): Vega-Cluster-Master on port lag-Intel6-2x25GE with IP 100.90.174.211/30; Vega-Cluster-Worker-1 on port lag-AFOR4-2x100GE with IP 172.24.245.216/31; Vega-Cluster-Worker-2 on port lag-Mellanox7-4x25GE with IP 100.105.107.83/24. Site 2 on device 192.168.132.118 (service ID 3188, RD 64639:3188, VRF QuantumNet-VRF-Import/QuantumNet-VRF-Export): Polaris-Cluster-Master on port lag-Intel6-4x25GE with IP 10.2.19.196/28; Polaris-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 2/2/c11/4 with IP 172.30.108.240/31; Polaris-Cluster-Worker-2 on port 1/2/c12/1 with IP 100.121.132.117/31."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-3188-QuantumNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 9085,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-3188-QuantumNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.168.88\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 3188,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"64533:3188\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"QuantumNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"QuantumNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Vega-Cluster-Master\"