{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Our network requires a new tunnel from 192.168.113.86 to 192.168.86.20 for service transport. SDP ID is 8620. Let's call it 'SDP-from-192-168-113-86-to-192-168-86-20'. Use BGP-based MPLS."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"tunnel\",\n  \"template_name\": \"MPLSTunnelsWithBGP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"source-ne-id\": \"192.168.113.86\",\n    \"sdp-id\": \"8620\",\n    \"destination-ne-id\": \"192.168.86.20\",\n    \"name\": \"SDP-from-192-168-113-86-to-192-168-86-20\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Please provision an E-Pipe between two routers. Details: Name='Epipe-VLAN-998-pop-to-datacenter', Customer=2186, ServiceID=2637, MTU=1400. Router A (192.168.189.142) port lag-AFOR8-4x10GE VLAN 998, Router B (192.168.84.113) port 1/1/c12/3 VLAN 998. SDP 142113 for A→B, SDP 113142 for B→A."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"epipe\",\n  \"template_name\": \"ePIPE-Service-Using-SDP\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"Epipe-VLAN-998-pop-to-datacenter\",\n    \"customer-id\": 2186,\n    \"ne-service-id\": 2637,\n    \"mtu\": 1400,\n    \"site-a.device-id\": \"192.168.189.142\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"lag-AFOR8-4x10GE\",\n    \"site-a.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 998,\n    \"site-b.device-id\": \"192.168.84.113\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].port-id\": \"1/1/c12/3\",\n    \"site-b.endpoint[0].outer-vlan-tag\": 998,\n    \"sdp[0].sdp-id\": \"142113\",\n    \"sdp[0].source-device-id\": \"192.168.189.142\",\n    \"sdp[0].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.84.113\",\n    \"sdp[1].sdp-id\": \"113142\",\n    \"sdp[1].source-device-id\": \"192.168.84.113\",\n    \"sdp[1].destination-device-id\": \"192.168.189.142\"\n  }\n}"}]}
{"messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "You are an NSP (Network Services Platform) intent configuration assistant. Given a natural language description of a network service, output a JSON object with three fields: 'intent_type' (one of: epipe, tunnel, vprn), 'template_name' (the NSP template to use), and 'fill_values' (a flat dictionary of field paths and their values that should be filled into the intent template). Only include fields that differ from template defaults. Use dot notation for nested paths and [N] for array indices. Output only valid JSON, no explanations."}, {"role": "user", "content": "I need a Layer 3 VPN for customer 3875. Name it 'VPRN-1866-HyperNet'. There's one site on device 192.168.231.53 with service ID 1866. Use RD 65210:1866, import policy HyperNet-VRF-Import and export policy HyperNet-VRF-Export. The interfaces are: Mercury-Cluster-Master on port 1/2/c12/4 with IP 10.203.240.137/28; Mercury-Cluster-Worker-1 on port 1/2/c10/2 with IP 10.38.7.214/24."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "{\n  \"intent_type\": \"vprn\",\n  \"template_name\": \"VPRNServiceTemplate\",\n  \"fill_values\": {\n    \"service-name\": \"VPRN-1866-HyperNet\",\n    \"customer-id\": 3875,\n    \"site[0].site-name\": \"VPRN-1866-HyperNet\",\n    \"site[0].device-id\": \"192.168.231.53\",\n    \"site[0].ne-service-id\": 1866,\n    \"site[0].route-distinguisher\": \"65210:1866\",\n    \"site[0].vrf-import\": [\n      \"HyperNet-VRF-Import\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].vrf-export\": [\n      \"HyperNet-VRF-Export\"\n    ],\n    \"site[0].interface[0].interface-name\": \"Mercury-Cluster-Master\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].sap.port-id\": \"1/2/c12/4\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.203.240.137\",\n    \"site[0].interface[0].ipv4.primary.prefix-length\": 28,\n    \"site[0].interface[1].interface-name\": \"Mercury-Cluster-Worker-1\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].sap.port-id\": \"1/2/c10/2\",\n    \"site[0].interface[1].ipv4.primary.address\": \"10.38